         <abstract id="aspace_0ab823d40d8f7f7a1a8b850168a2ec65">The Duke University Church
            (Interdenominational) was formed in response to the desire for a campus church at the
            University. The Church was founded in 1938 and disbanded in 1985. Types of materials
            include correspondence, financial material, minutes, and reports. Major subjects include
            Duke University religious life, students, Christianity, and fellowship. Materials range
            in date from 1936-1989 (bulk 1950-1979). English.</abstract>
